<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="1260">3.1.2. Validation process after ordering</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Once you’ve placed the order, you’ll receive a confirmation email (SSL Subscriber Agreement) from Sectigo.
Follow the instructions in the email to complete the validation process.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Generally speaking, there are two ways to proceed:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Follow the link in the email.
You will be forwarded to the Sectigo website.
There, enter the "verification code" that you received in the email. Follow the rest of the steps on the screen.
During the validation process, you will receive a phone call from Sectigo.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Download the documents listed in the email (Certificate Request Form &amp; SSL Subscriber Agreement).
Print the documents, sign them and send them back to Sectigo.
During the validation process, you will receive a phone call from Sectigo.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>It can take some time to complete all of the steps.
Leave yourself enough time to sign the forms, send them back to Sectigo, receive a phone call from Sectigo and complete the validation process.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Are you authorised to complete the process?</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The validation process must be completed by an authorised person, e.g. CIO or CEO.
During the process, legally binding documents need to be signed by someone with signatory rights.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="1280">3.2. In the setup menu</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>DV certificates (AlwaysOn and COMODO) are ordered in the Setup menu.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Ordering an SSL certificate in the Setup menu:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Client » Select client » SSL</strong>.<br>
→ The domain’s certificates are displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the row <strong>Order new SSL for domain: [domain name]</strong>, click on the down arrow to the right.<br>
→ The SSL certificates that are available for the domain are displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Check the available SSL certificates.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <span class="icon darkGrey"><i class="fa fa-shopping-cart  "></i></span> <strong>Order SSL certificate</strong> in the line of the SSL certificate that you want to book.<br>
→ The SSL certificate is ordered.<br>
<strong><em>Note:</em></strong> It can take up to 2 hours for the SSL certificate to be activated.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Delete the browser cache.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><em>Optional:</em></strong> Delete the DNS cache.</p>
<div class="olist loweralpha">
<ol class="loweralpha" type="a">
<li>
<p>Click the shortcut key <strong>Windows key + R</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter <code>CMD</code> and press <strong>Enter</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the command <code>ipconfig /flushdns</code>.<br>
→ The DNS cache is cleared.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
